"11:108:14" : {s: 11, a: 108, w: 14, r: "شيا", t: "شَآءَ", l: "شَآءَ", lc: 236, tl: "shāa", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "what your Lord wills", b: "ইচ্ছে করেন", i: "menghendaki", f: 56, rm: "to will/wish. shaiun (pl. ashyaaun) - thing/matter, affair in any way, at all, what is willed or wished, aught, any extent. In direct objective case it is often used to denote the meaning a little, bit, at all. Adverbially it means in any way, at all.", ag: "فعل ماض ", eg: "Verb Perfect ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "PERF", qual: "", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "شَآءَ،شَىْءٌۭ"},
"11:108:15" : {s: 11, a: 108, w: 15, r: "ربب", t: "رَبُّكَ", l: "رَبّ", lc: 975, tl: "rabbuka", lb: "প্রভু, সযত্নে পালনকর্তা",e: "what your Lord wills", b: "তোমার রব", i: "Tuhanmu", f: 42, rm: "to be a lord and master, collect, possess/owner, rule, increase, complete, bring up, preserve, chief, guardian, regulator, determiner, caretaker, provider, sustainer, perfecter, rewarder, creator, maintainer, reposer of properties, developer, former of rules and laws of the growth, foster a thing in such a manner as to make it attain one condition after another until it reaches its goal of completion, the bringing a thing to a state of completion by degrees, whoever possesses a thing is its rabb.", ag: "أسم مرفوع وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Nominative case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "NOM", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: ""},
"11:108:16" : {s: 11, a: 108, w: 16, r: "عطو", t: "عَطَآءً", l: "عَطَآء", lc: 5, tl: "ʿaṭāan", lb: "দান, উপহার",e: "a bestowal", b: "(তারা পাবে) পুরস্কার", i: "pemberian/karunia", f: 2, rm: "to take, receive. ataun - gift bestowment, present. ata - to give a present, offer. taata (vb. 6) - took.", ag: "أسم نكرة", eg: "Noun Indefinite state", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "INDEF", qual: "ACC", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: "أَعْطَىٰ،عَطَآءُ"},
"11:108:17" : {s: 11, a: 108, w: 17, r: "غير", t: "غَيْرَ", l: "غَيْر", lc: 147, tl: "ghayra", lb: "ব্যতীত",e: "not", b: "নয়", i: "tidak", f: 39, rm: "bring, convey, benefit, bestowed upon; alter or change a thing for the worse, corrupted, tainted, infected, render it ill-smelling; adjusting, repairing; difference between two persons; become jealous; procure; other than (exclusively), except, without; lies; [a man�s] dislike of another�s participation in what supposedly his right; care of what is sacred or inviolable to avoid suspicion of disdain; cognizance or badge of a free non-Muslim subjects in a Muslim government; one who puts off the furniture of his camel from off him to relieve and ease him. mughiraat - raiders.", ag: "أسم منصوب", eg: "Noun Accusative case", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACC", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: "غَيْرُ،يُغَيِّرُ"},
